!!! 5

%html
  %head
    %link{"href" => 'http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ubuntu&subset=latin', 'rel' => 'stylesheet', 'type' => 'text/css'}
    %link{"rel" => "stylesheet", "href" => "style.css", "type" => "text/css"}

    %script{"src" => "js/jquery.js", "type" => "text/javascript"}
    %script{"src" => "js/underscore-min.js", "type" => "text/javascript"}
    %script{"src" => "game.js", "type" => "text/javascript"}

    %title HTML5 Snake

  %body
    #templates
      #hud
        #playing
          %span#score-label Score:
          %span#score-value {{ score }}
        #lost
          #lost-text
            Loser! Your score is 
            %span#score-value {{ score }}
            %button#restart Play again!

    #content
      %h1.title Snake!
      #game
        #hud
        %canvas{"id" => "gamearea", "width" => "800", "height" => "400"}

      %p
        :markdown
          My first HTML5 game. Made with [HAML](http://haml-lang.com/), [SASS](http://sass-lang.com/) and [coffeescript](http://jashkenas.github.com/coffee-script/) by [me](http://twitter.com/#!tech_no_crat). Check out the code on [github](https://github.com/tech-no-crat/html5-snake). 
